    <section class="page" id="page-m1-5">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="16" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part I — Tracks by Mass</div>
        <h1>1.5 M☉ — The pp → CNO Transition</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Sits just above the ~1.2 M☉ threshold where the CNO cycle begins to compete with the pp chain — a small convective core, and degenerate helium ignition still on the menu at the RGB tip.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>Mixed pp / CNO</span><span>Small convective core</span><span>Degenerate He ignition</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page" id="page-m2-25">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="18" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part I — Tracks by Mass</div>
        <h1>2.25 M☉ — The M<sub>HeF</sub> Boundary</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Sits right at the ~2.2 M☉ line separating degenerate from non-degenerate helium ignition — the last mass with a genuine helium flash, and the first that could plausibly ignite helium quietly.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>M<sub>HeF</sub> ≈ 2.2 M☉</span><span>Flash/no-flash boundary</span><span>Short, poorly-populated RGB</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page" id="page-m3">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="20" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part I — Tracks by Mass</div>
        <h1>3 M☉ — Blue Loops</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Non-degenerate helium ignition and pronounced blue loops during core helium burning — repeated crossings of the Cepheid instability strip make this mass range central to distance-scale calibration.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>Quiet He ignition</span><span>Blue loops</span><span>Cepheid crossings</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
