    <section class="page" id="page-sunlike">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="18" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part II — The Six Fates</div>
        <h1>Sun-like Low-Mass (0.5–2 M☉)</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">The fate arc this whole prototype belongs to: degenerate helium ignition, a helium flash, horizontal branch, AGB, and a carbon-oxygen white dwarf — the Sun's own destiny.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>0.5–2 M☉</span><span>He flash</span><span>CO White Dwarf</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">This overview page will synthesize the individual mass tracks (0.5, 1, 1.5, 2.25 M☉) into a single fate narrative.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page" id="page-intermediate">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="24" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part II — The Six Fates</div>
        <h1>Intermediate (2–8 M☉)</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Quiet, non-degenerate helium ignition, blue loops, full thermally-pulsing AGB evolution, and a carbon-oxygen (or oxygen-neon) white dwarf at the end of the road.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>2–8 M☉</span><span>Quiet He ignition</span><span>CO / ONe WD</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page" id="page-massive-ns">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="30" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="4" fill="#7d7fa0"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part II — The Six Fates</div>
        <h1>Massive 8–25 M☉ → Neutron Star</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Builds a full onion-shell structure all the way to iron, then collapses catastrophically in a Type II supernova, leaving an ultra-dense neutron star behind.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>8–25 M☉</span><span>Core-collapse SN</span><span>Neutron star</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page" id="page-verymassive-bh">
      <div class="placeholder-wrap">
        <div class="ph-glyph"><svg width="60" height="60"><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="34" fill="none" stroke="#7d7fa0" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/><circle cx="30" cy="30" r="10" fill="#2a2c3a"/></svg></div>
        <div class="ph-badge">Part II — The Six Fates</div>
        <h1>Very Massive &gt;25 M☉ → Black Hole</h1>
        <p class="ph-desc">Powerful Wolf-Rayet winds strip the star bare before its iron core collapses so completely that not even a neutron star can hold — the end state is a stellar-mass black hole.</p>
        <div class="ph-meta"><span>M &gt; 25 M☉</span><span>Wolf-Rayet winds</span><span>Black hole</span></div>
        <p class="ph-note">Coming after the 1 M☉ prototype is approved.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</div>

<script>
(function(){
  var items = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item');
  var pages = document.querySelectorAll('.page');
  items.forEach(function(btn){
    btn.addEventListener('click', function(){
      items.forEach(function(b){ b.classList.remove('is-active'); });
      btn.classList.add('is-active');
      var target = btn.getAttribute('data-target');
      pages.forEach(function(p){ p.classList.toggle('is-active', p.id === target); });
      window.scrollTo(0,0);
    });
  });
})();
</script>
</body>
</html>
